a) All crew in the vicinity to wear suitable and appropriate PPE: overalls, safety shoes, hard hat, gloves, high-visibility vest, etc.; 
b) Adequate lighting to be provided; 
c) Suitable warning notices should be posted; 
d) Access to the area must be restricted; 
e) All crew / personnel not directly involved in crane operations should stay well clear.

a) Use of suitable and appropriate PPE: overalls, safety shoes, hard hat, gloves, high-visibility vest, etc.; 
b) Adequate lighting to be provided; 
c) Communication must be established, via VHF or crane signals, between the crane operator and crew working below; 
d) The cargo crane hook should be clearly painted; 
e) All crew / personnel not directly involved in crane operations should stay well clear.

a) Maintenance and inspections to be carried out in accordance with the Manufacturer's Manual and Company MPM system; 
b) The cargo crane wires should be visually inspected and condition checked prior to every use; 
c) Wires found in poor condition or damaged must be replaced immediately; 
d) The cargo crane hook, including safety latch and springs should be visually inspected and condition checked prior to every use; 
e) All lifting accessories should be visually inspected and condition check prior to use; 
f) When not in use, all lifting accessories should be stored accordingly, protected by the elements.

a) The crane operator must be informed of any person(s) climbing up the crane; 
b) Under no circumstances should any person(s) embark / disembark the ladders whilst the crane is rotating; 
c) Adequate lighting to be provided.

a) All crew involved have the necessary training and full understanding of signal procedures; 
b) The signalman must be positioned were they can be visually seen by the crane operator; 
c) VHFs should be used were possible.

a) All crew involved to be briefed; 
b) VHF radio check prior to operations; 
c) Use of the English language in clear and concise orders; 
d) Use of headphones, if necessary, in conjunction with the VHF.
